snippet: This winter season, the true triumph of New York City Ballet lay in the way its corps de ballet danced some works by its co-founder George Balanchine.
abstract: Alastair Macaulay asserts true triumph of New York City Ballet's winter season lay not in any individual performance, but in the way that its corps de ballet danced some works by co-founder George Balanchine.
lead_paragraph: This winter season, the true triumph of New York City Ballet lay in the way its corps de ballet danced some works by its co-founder George Balanchine.

headline.seo: Taking Stock of City Ballet’s Secret Weapon
